        <body>

            <pb n="1"/>

            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>St. Louis&#44; Missouri&#44;</placeName>
                <date>June 24&#44; 1857.</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>&#58;</p>

            <p rend="indent(1)">Honored Sir&#58; Although three weeks<lb/>
 ago I notified you that I am functioning
                here<lb/>
 as Chazan and Schochet&#44; I take the liberty<lb/>
 to inform you now that
                I have taken on a<lb/>
 schochet at my own expense and have or&#8211;<lb/>
ganized a
                school for the young where Hebrew<lb/>
 is taught. <persName>Mr. Lattin</persName>
                and <persName>Mr. Meyer</persName>
<lb/>
 told me that you have published works
                &#40;guides&#63;&#41; for<lb/>
 the instruction of youthful beginners&#44; and<lb/>
                that there are several copies here but not<lb/>
 sufficient. That is why I beg of
                you&#44; honored<lb/>
 sir&#44; to send two or three dozen to <persName>Mr.
                    Lattin</persName>
<lb/>
 or to me&#44; as well as several prayer books<lb/>
 and
                other such things. My request is that you<lb/>
 send it as soon as possible. I also
                request<lb/>
 my bill that I owe&#44; in order that I might<lb/>
 take care of it.
                Conditions with regard to the<lb/>
 youth here are pitiful. It has been
                neglec<lb/>
ted. I hope&#44; with God&#39;s help&#44; to accomplish<lb/>
 much.<lb/>
</p>
<p rend="indent(1)">I beg to inform you that the con&#8211;<lb/>
gregation will soon begin the building
                of<lb/>
 a <sic>cynagogue</sic>&#44; <del>with</del> with where the school<lb/>
</p>

<pb n="2"/>
<p>will be housed.</p>
<p rend="indent(1)">Finally&#44; I want to ask you to<lb/>
 notify me who those
                gentlemen are&#44; and<lb/>
 to note whether they are behind-hand&#44; who<lb/>
 are
                subscribers to the &#8220;Occident&#8221;. Also&#44; the<lb/>
 term of each. I shall
                go round and<lb/>
 collect everything for you&#44; and gather<lb/>
 subscriptions&#44;
                and instead of 30 per month<lb/>
 make it 30 per week. If you are satisfied&#44;<lb/>
                I want to be your agent.</p>
<p rend="indent(1)">Your friend&#44;<lb/>
<persName role="author">H. Kuttner</persName>
<lb/>
 c/o <persName>Joseph
                    Kohn</persName>
<lb/>
<placeName>St. Louis&#44; MO</placeName>
<lb/>
 Please send six dozen. It cost the
                same<lb/>
 thing by express.<lb/>
</p>

</body>
